.\" Manpage.
.\" To correct errors or typos.
.TH man_simple_shell  "13 April 2021" "Holberton School 0x16. C - Simple_Shell"

.SH NAME 
0x16. C - Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS 
Simple-Shell it is a box where you put commands and these are interpreted by itself

.SH DESCRIPTION 
A Unix shell is a command-line interpreter or shell that provides a command line user interface for Unix-like operating systems. 
The shell is both an interactive command language and a scripting language, and is used by the operating system to control the execution of the system using shell scripts.

.SH BUGS 
No known bugs.

.SH ENVIRONMENT 
HOME contains the user's directory
USER contains the user's login
PWD contains current directory
SHELL contains the name of the connection shell
PATH contains the list of directories where the commands that the user can execute are located
HOSTNAME contains the hostname
HOSTSIZE contains the maximum size of the executed commands contained in the archive file
PS1 contains the configuration for displaying the prompt

.SH AUTHORS
Jaime Garcia
